item.title: How to Install the MacOS(Sierra) on the Kali (Virtual Box) .
item.dc:creator: dangwalbharat
item.content:encoded:
MacOS is always a very fascinating stuff to have with you, but if you don't have one and you still wanna use it then I do have some simple methods which can help you in installing the same. So that you can fulfill your MacOS dream in any other laptop.

  1. DOWNLOAD

Lets Start Downloading the ISO for the MacOS.

MacOS Image

2. Download the Virtual Box

To install the Virtual Box in the kali . Run the following commands and you are ready to go.

a) Open the terminal.

b) sudo apt update && apt upgrade

c) sudo apt install virtualbox.

3. Open Virtual Box and Setup the Setting of MacOS.

a) Open Virtual Box , click on tools and select new.

b) Name as MacOS , Machine Folder where your device will store the data, Type will come by default as Mac OS X and Version as Mac OS X(64-bit) by default.

c) Select Memory Size Minimum 8 GB else it will be very slow and you won't have good experience. Click Next.

d) Select Create a Virtual hard disk now and Click on Create.

e) Click on the VDI and click Next .

f) Click on the Dynamically allocated, so that we can give large space to Virtual OS , but it will use the same OS which you are using. Click Next.

g) Now mention here 80.00 GB as Dynamically allocated space to the MacOS and Click on Create.

h) Open the MacOS VM Box setting, by clicking on the MacOS right click Settings.

i) Click on Setting -> System -> Processor. Make it at-least 2.

j) Change the Display setting -> Screen tab -> Video Memory to maximum.

k) Click on Storage and Input ISO image in the empty slot there.

l) Disable the Network as it is not attached and click on the OK button.

4. Start Installation.

a) Now we have to make some setting for the MacOS in the VMBox. we have to run to make this script in bash and need to run in machine . We can run the script with the following commands( bash MacOS.sh)

b) After running this script, Select the MacOS in the VM and Click on Start.

c) Install with begin with some CLI commands(verbose mode) need to wait till we will reach to the next screen with Installation Process. Process can take time depending on the processor speed.

d) Few steps more and your MacOS will be ready soon .

e) Select the Language English and Click on arrow sign. ( You can choose as per your Local Language)

f) Select on Install macOS and Click Continue.

g) After clicking on Continue, Error message. Oh no ! we made some mistake.

h) Don't worry, its nothing just a date & time based issue. We need to adjust the time here. Click on OK and pop up window will close, now click on the Utilities on the top and open the terminal. Check the current date and update the date like below image. For better reference video is attached. Try the method systematically and it will work, while i choose the 2nd method .

i) If you have SSD in your system then you have to make few more change as SSD won't be detect by MacOS directly. lets make few more changes which can be done by terminal only. Follow the below steps.

j) Type diskutil list and you can see the disk0 on your name drive. (Checking the Disk)

k) Type diskutil eraseDisk JHFS+ MacOS /dev/disk0. (Formatting the Disk)

l)Type diskutil apfs createContainer /dev/disk0s2. disk0s2 is new name which we get after formatting the disk0, it is mentioned in the above step. (Format the disk0s2 to disk21) disk

m) Type diskutil apfs addVolume disk21 APFS MacOS1. (Adding the Disk)

n) Now select Install macOS and click Continue. Here we are.

o) Click on Continue and then click on Agree after then Select the disk where you want to install macOS. Select the Harddisk and Click on Install.

p) Once you click Install, and OS will install automatically. This process will restart your system and install the MacOS, Process will take some time, till the time you can have some coffee.

q) Once the installation will done it will ask to create account.

Bravo! ... It's done , just fill your basic details and you are ready to go.

item.title: How to Install Windows Server 2016 (Core) on Virtual Machine.
item.dc:creator: dangwalbharat
item.content:encoded:
Windows are always user friendly because of its Graphical User Interface(GUI) nature, so everyone loves that. Its very easy to use , user just need to make few clicks to do anything like installation , opening any application , closing an application etc. Now , Imagine suddenly all the GUI is gone and we are left with Command Line Interface(CLI). That will be a tough nut to crack, if you don't have previous experience with CLI. So no need to worry Let's just solve this issue by installing the 2016 Server based window on Core(CLI Version).

Download the Windows 2016 Server Image.

Here I consider myself as user which has knowledge about the VM Installation and has already installed the VM. If not please click here.

Once you are done with Installation, Lets download the Windows 2016 Server Image.

Above link will direct you to the page of download and then you have to click on the ISO to Continue . After that it will ask for few details which you need to fill them.

After filling the basic details, it will ask you the preference of language in which you want to download. You can choose your language as per you requirement.

Once you select the Language, then click on the Download. Image will start downloading automatically you just need to save it.

Set up the Virtual Machine for the Windows Server 2016 Installation.

Once downloading is finish, then we have to setup the Virtual Box for installation of the Windows Server.

Open Virtual Box, Click on the Tools and then Click on New. Give the Name to the Operating System as we already know it is Windows 2016 Server so lets make it W2K16.

Click on Next, to select the RAM. Make sure you must choose the RAM within the Green Mark only. As Green mark suggest the free space of RAM in your system. Here we are using 4 GB RAM.

After clicking on the Next, you need to choose the hard-disk. So, Here we are selecting 2 option i.e Create a virtual disk now and then click on Create.

Once you click on create it will ask for Hard disk file type, so here we are selecting option 2 and option 3. So we will select option 2 and click on Next.

After that we need to select the Storage on physical hard disk, either we have Dynamically allocated or Fixed Size. But our preference is on Dynamically allocated as it will save space in the Hard disk if it is not used. After selecting the Dynamically, click Next.

Now we have select the file location and size. our suggestion is to provide at-least 80GB, and location can be changed according to the user. After choosing proper location and providing proper space click on Create.

Now we can see 1 new Virtual Machine in your Virtual Box. Before making any change in the setting of the Virtual Machine. Let's make Nat Network without DHCP. Click on the file option -> Preferences.

Go to the Network and Create new NAT network, make sure to disable the DHCP and IPV6 support. We will provide the manual IP to the server.

Now select the new created Virtual Machine named as W2K16 and click on the Settings. Go to the Storage option and select the ISO image in the Empty Disk of the Storage Device.

After selecting the ISO image lets select the Network option as NAT Network which has been created above Nat and click on OK.

Install the Windows Server 2016.

Now we have ultimately reached from where we can install the Windows Server 2016. Lets Select W2K16 and click on Start on the Virtual Box and it will bootup and installation process will begin.

Select the Language, Time, Currency and Keyboard according to your place. After that click on Next. Once we Click on Next it will prompt us to new window which shows Install now. Click on Install now.

Once we click on Install Now, Window Setup process will start. It will prompt us with 4 options for installation 2 are based on GUI and 2 are based CLI. So we will install CLI based Standard Evaluation i.e Option 1. Select 1 and click on Next.

Accept the License term and Click on Next.

Now as we are doing fresh install so we have to select Custom Option.

Once we click the Custom, it will prompt us to next screen where we can install the windows. we had already took 80 GB as hard disk, so we won't make any partition and select 1 as complete, further we can make partition according to our requirements.

Once we click Next , Installation will begin automatically and it will show screen like this.

Installation can take time depending on the system. So meanwhile we can have some coffee. During Installation process system will reboot automatically, System will be reboot for 2 times. After that it will direct us to the password input. User need to create a new password.

Once the password has been set properly then we are ready to work with new CLI based Windows Server 2016.

It's Done. I hope with this Blog, you can install the windows server 2016 Desktop version without any problem. If I miss something you want to add. Please let me know and share your thought. Thank you.

item.title: How to Solve the OWASP Juice Shop Exercise in Tryhackme.
item.dc:creator: dangwalbharat
item.content:encoded:
Tryhackme is a platform to enhance your testing skills. There are plenty of rooms available to learn and practice your skills inside the tryhackme, so lets try to solve 1 of the room(Juice Shop).

Prerequisites
  • Login Details for Tryhackme.(Signup if you are a new user.)
  • Burp Suit
TASK 1

It is clearly mention that connection with OWASP Juice Shop machine is only possible when user will connect to the Tryhackme network, so we need to download the network configuration file. Lets click on the guide link which is provided on Task1. Once you click there it directs you to different pages from where you need to download the configuration file.

Click on the Download My Configuration File which is in green color, from here it is clear that user need to use the VPN to connect with the machine. After you download the file you have to open the Terminal and type openvpn file.ovpn. (file is the name of configuration file which is downloaded from the Tryhackme).

Once you connect to the VPN properly refresh the above page and you will see the changes in Network Information and after that it will be connected.

After getting network status on, you have to click on Deploy as an icon which is in Task1, Once you click on deploy the server will provide you with an IP address.

Now once you get the IP from the server wait atleast for 7-10 mins and then copy paste the IP in another new tab.

Once the IP will open, now you can mark the exercise as complete.

TASK 2

All the things are clearly mentioned by Tryhackme team . In the post you will find all the necessary details which has been required . User has to just configure in the same way. After verifying the configuration operation if it works then we can mark it as complete.

TASK 3

It is very much clear that they want you to review the website and need to understand the operation of the same, for that let's visit different pages and different section to understand about the website.

After visiting all the pages which are available in the upfront, It is clear that this is an Online juice website and user can place order from here and this website can perform some functions like online selling portal , customer feedback , review of product etc. Let's mark this as complete now.

TASK 4

This task is about the SQL injection, this want us to bypass the login page. Open the IP and visit the login page.

Once you open the Login page. Lets try some random login to check whether this page is vulnerable to sql injection or not.

It is not clear that the page is vulnerable to sql injection but it is clear that it has some issues and that cannot be handled properly . So lets try some proper injection. With login details of email : ' or 1=1 -- and password can be anything, as we are saying just ignore everything after 1=1.

Wohoo! now lets login again and you will see that we just bypass the login page and we got the confirmation from the server side also.

Lets mark this exercise as complete.

TASK 5

a) This task is divided into 2 different segments. First task is to reset Jim's password by using the forgotten password mechanism for that you need to get the Secret question answer. Lets first visit the forgotten password page.

To go ahead we need to get the Jim email id. Lets search email id first. In Previous task I was able to bypass the admin login. Lets revisit the admin and try to visit some more common web pages like /admin , /administrator , /administration etc.

Bravo .....! After trying some well known pages we managed to get the details of all the users in the portal. From here we can see that there is a user with Email as jim@juice-sh.op. Lets use this email id.

Now here comes the tricky question, we have to answer the sibling middle name. But who is Jim? we need to find out. Lets search the website again. After going through all the pages we can see there are 2 review by the Jim on the product.

After reading the comments, it is clear that these are not usual comments, so try to find out on internet.

It's very unusual that both comments are redirecting towards Star Trek. Let's search for Jim in the Star Trek now.

OMG......! There is someone with name James T. Krik. Lets open the page and read about him. After reading the article , we got to know that he has a brother named George Samuel Kirk. Its very strange but lets try it.

WOW!..... it works. It was a difficult one but eventually I crack it.

Lets move ahead toward Task 2 in which we need to find the admin password.

Now we already have the admin email id but we need to search the password, lets try with some random password in the login page. After trying few random password we can see that there is no limitation on number of attempts, so we can try some brute forcing.

Lets intercept with the help of Burp Suite.

For Brute forcing of the login page, we need to send the request to intruder. Just press CTRL+I. We can see on the right side that there is a Clear option. Click on it and then select the Password after that click on Add. This will allow us to brute force only password.

Once we are done with adding, lets change the tab from Position to Payloads, and put some random payload for password. Payload means that there is a password which we want to test against this username. So I created a small list of those passwords.

Now Just click on the attack button on the right side of the same page. Once we press the click, it will start to check all the password against the username 1 by 1.

Here we can see that there is 1 result which is different from all . And Status is also 200. That means OK. From here we got the password as admin123.

Both challenges are solved.

TASK 6

We need to find some confidential document.

Lets search the website again with basic /robots.txt. (IP changes as session expired and this is a new session, server provide IP only for 1 hour session)

Here we can see that there is /ftp path which is disallow. Let's check this path.

Here we saw the acquisitions.md and question ask for the first file with .md extension.

Challenge has been solved.

TASK 7

There are 3 part inside this task. Let's solve them 1 by 1.

a) We need to access the administration section of the store and we have already done this in above part.

b) Need to Access someone else's basket. Lets create the new user and login with same.

After login let's add some product in the basket and try to check-out.

Let's open the developer mode i.e press f12 key in Mozilla Firefox. Click on the Storage and here you will see a bid Value as 4.

Let's try to change the value of bid as 3 and refresh the page. You can see that we are still in test user but this is not our basket as our basket has multiple items.

We just solved the challenge.

c) Get rid of all 5 star customer feedback.

Remember we had already visited the administration page, now let's revisit the page again . For that we need to log out from the test user and login as admin.

After visiting the page on right side we can see that there is a 5 star rating on Customer Feedback. Just click on the bin icon near it.

Yayy !.... , we cracked it .

TASK 8

Yes, finally we reach to our last Task. lets just finish this one. We have 2 task in this series . lets do it 1 by 1.

a) Carry out reflected XSS using Tracking orders. Login again with test user and place some random order and then visit the Tracking order pages.

Click on the Juice icon and then Track Orders.

Lets enter some basic javascript to check, as it clearly mention need to apply XSS on this <script>alert(1)</script> and click on Track.

This is not working and there is no output. So Let's try some other script. <img src=x onerror=javascript:alert(1)//"> and click on the Track.

b) Carry out XSS using search field. In this we have to apply the XSS in the search field.

Start with basic of xss <script>alert(1)</script> and press search button.

No output that means we need to use some other script. Try this one <svg/onload=alert(1)> and press search button.

We got the output and xss works.

Finally we have solved all the challenges.
